  "title": "HR Manager (Talent Acquisition) (Ref 26064)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Lead and manage a team of 8, providing guidance, mentorship, and performance management.<br />• Co-develop and implement strategic talent acquisition plans to meet the organization's hiring needs.<br />• Ensure operational excellence in all recruitment processes and procedures.<br />• Stay abreast of industry trends and best practices in talent acquisition, continuously improving our recruitment strategies.<br />• Analyze recruitment metrics and provide regular reports to senior management.<br />• Foster relationships with stakeholders (internal and external) including hiring managers, agencies, educational institutes, etc.<br /><br />Requirements<br />• Bachelor's degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field<br />• Minimum of 10 years of experience in talent acquisition or a similar role, preferably in healthcare or a related industry<br />• Proven track record of leading and developing high-performing recruitment teams<br />• Proven track record of fulfilling high acquisition volume<br />• Strong understanding of recruitment best practices and trends<br />• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills<br />• Demonstrated ability to develop and implement strategic hiring plans<br />• Meticulous attention to detail and strong organizational skills<br />• Proactive approach to problem-solving and decision-making<br /></p><p>Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
